________________________________________
##Key Concepts Learned
•	request.time is the IAM attribute used to evaluate time based access
•	IAM Conditions are evaluated at request time, not creation time
•	IAM allows multiple conditional bindings for the same identity+role
•	If ANY conditional binding evaluates TRUE → permission granted
•	Temporary access windows can override longer term business-hour restrictions
•	Removal of a condition requires matching: 
o	title
o	description
o	expression

•	The Google Cloud CLI escapes operators visually (&lt;=, &gt;=, &amp;&amp;) but IAM stores real operators (<=, >=, &&)
•	Impersonation requires roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator on the target service account
•	Service account impersonation produces short-lived OAuth tokens, not files
•	Blank gcloud storage ls output = success on empty buckets
